                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" class="TableCell"><b>Home again</b><br>
                                 As written by Josh Harrison on April 19, 2004 3:23 PM
                                 <p></p>
                                 The group returned to Valyan's Legacy, and told Banstar's mentor Cedric that his student had fallen in battle with a Horror.
                                 They also told Erthan and Valin, Kelric's parents, that he had died as well.<p/>They were invited to a ceremony where the
                                 two fallen comrades had their names inscribed on a memorial to the fallen Defenders of the Legacy. Kira and Rezak were sworn
                                 in as new Defenders, carrying on the work of their late friends.<p/>That afternoon, they found a group of green recruits poring
                                 excitedly over a map -- which bore a striking resemblance to the map the group had been carrying for the past few months.
                                 The story of how they had obtained this map bore a strong resemblance to the group's own experience... suspicious, the group
                                 joined forces with the other party in hopes of uncovering whatever plot was in motion.<p/>The next few days were uneventful,
                                 as they groups followed the map. Then, early on their fifth day of travel, they came upon a box canyon with the unmistakable
                                 large stone doors of a kaer set in the mountainside.<p/>Expecting an ambush, the group carefully approached the doors. Despite
                                 their caution, the group sprung the ambush. About a dozen archers rained arrows down on the group, which took shelter in the
                                 kaer entrance. Rezak and Gir tried to escape back up the canyon, only to be captured by more bandits (led by a troll Warrior)
                                 who were blocking the exit. In the ensuing struggle, Rezak was killed in a hail of arrows.<p/>Thrak managed to rescue Gir,
                                 and took her back into the kaer, where they slammed the doors shut behind them. Now the eight adepts are locked in a kaer,
                                 with an angry bandit gang outside, and who knows what perils inside...
                                 <br></td>
                           </tr>
                        </table>
