                           <tr>
                              <td width="100%" class="TableCell"><b>Escape and Revenge</b><br>
                                 As written by Josh Harrison on April 27, 2004 10:47 AM
                                 <p></p>
                                 Soon after Thrak slammed the door to the kaer, Kira heard the distinctive sound of the chain and lock being put back across
                                 the outside.<p/>With nothing better to do, the group set out to explore the kaer. All evidence indicated that the kaer was
                                 long abandoned -- aside from some broken rock and bits of trash, there was nothing of real value to be found.<p/>One of the
                                 rooms in the kaer had a series of murals that depicted the history of the kaer -- from its founding and construction to its
                                 betrayal and destruction by the very person who founded it.<p/>Further exploration uncovered the kaer's throne room, and the
                                 secret -- and unwarded -- passage to the surface. The passage was guarded by the cursed, undead spirit of the former lord
                                 who built and betrayed the kaer. After a brief but intense fight, the king was defeated, and his gem-encrusted treasures were
                                 recoverered.<p/>Rather than rush to the surface, the group spent a couple days holed up in the kaer, healing their wounds
                                 from the fight with the bandits and the undead king.<p/>They finally emerged into the sunlight, and tracked the bandits back
                                 to their camp. While scouting, Kira had the opportunity to steal the bandit leader's bow. She took to opportunity, and flew
                                 off with it. The rest of the group attacked, and defeated the bandit leader, his troll lieutenant, and the bandits present
                                 in the camp.<p/>The group made plans to return to Valyan's Legacy to see if they could sell the loot taken from the undead
                                 king and the bandit camp.
                                 <br></td>
                           </tr>
